SIMPLE: streamer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Streamer
<hw>Stream"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An
ensign, flag, or pennant, which floats in the wind; specifically, a
long, narrow, ribbonlike flag.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Brave Rupert from afar appears,⟦br⟧
Whose waving <qex>streamers</qex> the glad general knows.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A stream or column of light shooting upward from the
horizon, constituting one of the forms of the aurora borealis.</def>
<rj><au>Macaulay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>While overhead the North's dumb <qex>streamers</qex> shoot.</q>
<rj><qau>Lowell.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Mining)</fld> <def>A searcher for stream
tin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Journalism)</fld> <def>a banner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Streamful</ent>⟦br⟧
